quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  2,60,"When Moses, too, asked drink for his people and We said, \"Strike with your staff the rock,\" and from it burst forth twelve springs; each tribe among them knew his drinking place. \"Eat and drink of what Allah has provided, and transgress not"
  2,61,"And when they said: \"Moses, we cannot always bear one kind of food; pray then to your Lord to bring forth for us of what the earth grows, its green herbs, its cucumbers, its garlic, its lentils, and its onions.\" Said He, \"Do you ask what is"
  2,62,"Verily, whether it be of those who believe, or those who are Jews or Christians or Sabaeans, whoever believes in Allah and the Last Day and acts aright, they have their reward with their Lord, and there is no fear for them, nor shall they grieve"
  2,63,"And when We took a covenant with you and held the mountain over you; (saying) \"Accept what We have brought you with strong will, and bear in mind what is therein, per chance (or possibly) you yet may fear"
  2,64,"Then even after that did you turn aside, and were it not for Allah´s grace towards you and His mercy, you would have been of those who lose"
  2,65,"You know also of those among you who transgressed upon the Sabbath, and how We said to them, \"Be you (as) apes, despised and spurned"
  2,66,"Thus We made them an example unto those who stood before them, and those who should come after them, and a warning unto those who fear Allah"
  2,67,"And remember when Moses said to his people, \"Allah bids you slaughter a heifer.\" they said, \"Are you making a jest of us?\" Said he, \"I seek refuge with Allah from being one of the unwise"
  2,68,"They said, \"Then pray to your Lord for us to show us what she is to be.\" He answered, \"He said it is a cow, not old, nor young, of middle age between the two; so do as you are bid"
  2,69,"They said, \"Pray now to your Lord to show us what her colour is to be.\" He answered, \"He said it is a fawn-coloured heifer, intensely fawn, her colour delighting those who look upon her"
  2,70,"Again they said, \"Pray to your Lord to show us what she is to be; for cows appear the same to us; then we, if Allah will, shall be guided"
  2,71,"He answered, \"He said, it is a heifer, not broken in to plough the earth or irrigate the tilth, a sound one with no blemish on her.\" They said, \"Now have you brought the truth.\" And they slaughtered her, though they came near leaving i"
  2,72,"Remember when you slew a soul and disputed thereupon, and Allah brought forth that which you had hidden"
  2,73,"Then We said, \"Strike him with part of her (the heifer).\" Thus Allah brings the dead to life and shows you His signs, that per chance (or possibly) you may understand"
  2,74,"Yet were your heart hardened even after that, till they were as rocks or harder still, for verily, there are some rocks from which streams burst forth, and others burst asunder and water issues out, and others there are that sink down for fear of Allah; b"